<subSubSection lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="14" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="12.[264,1324,1135,1881]" box="[264,383,1135,1160]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis box="[264,383,1135,1160]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[264,1324,1135,1881]" box="[312,959,1175,1201]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Large flies, males 
<quantity box="[527,685,1175,1201]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" metricValueMax="1.1199999999999999" metricValueMin="0.88" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="10.0" valueMax="11.2" valueMin="8.8">8.8–11.2 mm</quantity>
, females 
<number box="[795,832,1175,1201]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="9.4">9.4</number>
–12.0 mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[264,1324,1135,1881]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,385,1214,1240]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Head.</emphasis>
Ocellar tubercle dark reddish brown, pruinescence gray, not raised above level of vertex in males; setae dark reddish brown, elongate. Eyes reddish brown, anterior margin sinuate; dichoptic in males and females, separated by distance greater than width of ocellar tubercle; ommatidia of equal size. Frons reduced in males; black band absent lateral to antennal base; setae extending lateral to antennal base. Face projecting moderately beyond anterior margin of eyes. Antenna shorter than head length; scape cylindrical, about two times longer than wide, over two times length of pedicel, subequal in width to flagellum, setae dark brown, elongate, macrosetae dark brown, absent on medial surface; pedicel globular, wider than long, setae short, absent on medial surface; first flagellomere oval, tapered apically, second flagellomere cylindrical, short, third flagellomere globular, short, flagellum over two times longer than wide and slightly longer than length of scape; apical style short. Parafacial setae absent. Maxillary palpus cylindrical, apex slightly clavate. Gena rounded ventrally, lacking anterodorsal patch of short setae. Occipital macrosetae dark reddish brown to black (&gt; 
<number box="[1020,1053,1735,1761]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="50.0">50</number>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[264,1324,1135,1881]" box="[264,771,1775,1801]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Postocular macrosetae black, in single row.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[264,1324,1135,1881]" lastBlockId="13.[264,1323,284,1756]" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="14" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,412,1814,1840]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Thorax.</emphasis>
Macrosetae 
<number box="[561,605,1815,1841]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="4.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="2.0">2–6</number>
np, 
<number box="[656,700,1815,1841]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2</number>
sa, 
<number box="[746,761,1815,1841]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1.0">1</number>
pa, 
<number box="[810,854,1815,1841]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="3.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="1.0">1–6</number>
dc, 
<number box="[903,918,1815,1841]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="2.0">2</number>
dc. Postpronotal lobe concolorous with mesonotum. Cervical sclerite lacking setae and macrosetae. Prosternum lacking setae in and around central depression. Setae absent on proepimeron, anepimeron, meron, and metakatepisternum. 
<emphasis box="[502,570,324,349]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Wing.</emphasis>
Setulae absent on dorsal surface of R 
<number box="[1011,1019,340,354]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1.0">1</number>
; cell m 
<number box="[1106,1114,340,354]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="3.0">3</number>
open widely; M 
<number box="[1307,1315,340,354]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1.0">1</number>
, M 
<number box="[290,298,383,397]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="2.0">2</number>
, and M 
<number box="[394,402,383,397]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="3.0">3</number>
originate separately from apex of discal cell; cell 
<emphasis box="[1011,1054,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">cup</emphasis>
closed, petiolate; anal angle broadly rounded; alula rounded. 
<emphasis box="[747,810,410,435]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Legs.</emphasis>
Coxae dark brown, pruinescence whitish gray, dense; setae white, elongate; setae absent on posterior half of midcoxa; hindcoxa with papillate anterior knob and one posterolateral macroseta; apical macrosetae and posterolateral macroseta on hindcoxa pale yellow. Femora lacking lanceolate, appressed setae dorsally; av absent on fore­ and midfemur, pv absent.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="13.[264,1323,284,1756]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,441,609,635]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Abdomen.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[449,639,610,635]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Male 
<taxonomicName box="[517,639,610,635]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Combretaceae" genus="Terminalia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="13" pageNumber="23" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">terminalia</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
. Tergite 
<number box="[744,759,610,636]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="8.0">8</number>
(
<figureCitation box="[775,864,610,636]" captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 29" captionStartId="19.[264,382,1605,1629]" captionTargetBox="[296,1306,324,1572]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[249,1338,305,1582]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 29. Peralia vittata. 20. Tergite 8, epandrium, cerci, hypoproct, dorsal view. 21. Sternite 8, gonocoxite, ventral view. 22. Gonocoxite, dorsal view. 23. Gonocoxite, lateral view. 24. Gonostylus, lateral view. 25. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 26. Aedeagus, ventral view. 27. Aedeagus, lateral view. 28. Female internal reproductive organs. Peralia hermanni. 29. Female internal reproductive organs. Scale = 0.1 mm. Abbreviation: LEP = lateral ejaculatory process, SpSd = spermathecal sac duct." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173538/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Fig. 
<number box="[831,864,610,636]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="20.0">20</number>
</figureCitation>
), posterior margin broadly emarginate; median length thick (&gt; 
<quantity box="[535,642,650,676]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" unit="mm" value="0.05">0.05 mm</quantity>
); setae generally absent medially on posterior margin; one pair of sensory setae. Sternite 
<number box="[635,650,690,716]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="8.0">8</number>
(
<figureCitation box="[670,758,690,716]" captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 29" captionStartId="19.[264,382,1605,1629]" captionTargetBox="[296,1306,324,1572]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[249,1338,305,1582]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 29. Peralia vittata. 20. Tergite 8, epandrium, cerci, hypoproct, dorsal view. 21. Sternite 8, gonocoxite, ventral view. 22. Gonocoxite, dorsal view. 23. Gonocoxite, lateral view. 24. Gonostylus, lateral view. 25. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 26. Aedeagus, ventral view. 27. Aedeagus, lateral view. 28. Female internal reproductive organs. Peralia hermanni. 29. Female internal reproductive organs. Scale = 0.1 mm. Abbreviation: LEP = lateral ejaculatory process, SpSd = spermathecal sac duct." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173538/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Fig. 
<number box="[728,758,690,716]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="21.0">21</number>
</figureCitation>
) quadrate, anterior margin truncate to slightly emarginate, posterior margin truncate; setae continuous across posterior margin. Epandrium (
<figureCitation box="[416,508,770,796]" captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 29" captionStartId="19.[264,382,1605,1629]" captionTargetBox="[296,1306,324,1572]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[249,1338,305,1582]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 29. Peralia vittata. 20. Tergite 8, epandrium, cerci, hypoproct, dorsal view. 21. Sternite 8, gonocoxite, ventral view. 22. Gonocoxite, dorsal view. 23. Gonocoxite, lateral view. 24. Gonostylus, lateral view. 25. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 26. Aedeagus, ventral view. 27. Aedeagus, lateral view. 28. Female internal reproductive organs. Peralia hermanni. 29. Female internal reproductive organs. Scale = 0.1 mm. Abbreviation: LEP = lateral ejaculatory process, SpSd = spermathecal sac duct." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173538/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Fig. 
<number box="[477,508,770,796]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="20.0">20</number>
</figureCitation>
) shorter medially than wide; anterior margin broadly emarginate; posterolateral margin short, broadly pointed. Cercus (
<figureCitation box="[886,971,810,836]" captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 29" captionStartId="19.[264,382,1605,1629]" captionTargetBox="[296,1306,324,1572]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[249,1338,305,1582]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 29. Peralia vittata. 20. Tergite 8, epandrium, cerci, hypoproct, dorsal view. 21. Sternite 8, gonocoxite, ventral view. 22. Gonocoxite, dorsal view. 23. Gonocoxite, lateral view. 24. Gonostylus, lateral view. 25. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 26. Aedeagus, ventral view. 27. Aedeagus, lateral view. 28. Female internal reproductive organs. Peralia hermanni. 29. Female internal reproductive organs. Scale = 0.1 mm. Abbreviation: LEP = lateral ejaculatory process, SpSd = spermathecal sac duct." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173538/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Fig. 
<number box="[940,971,810,836]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="20.0">20</number>
</figureCitation>
) free, oblong; ending distal to posterolateral margin of epandrium. Hypoproct (
<figureCitation box="[878,973,850,876]" captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 29" captionStartId="19.[264,382,1605,1629]" captionTargetBox="[296,1306,324,1572]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[249,1338,305,1582]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 29. Peralia vittata. 20. Tergite 8, epandrium, cerci, hypoproct, dorsal view. 21. Sternite 8, gonocoxite, ventral view. 22. Gonocoxite, dorsal view. 23. Gonocoxite, lateral view. 24. Gonostylus, lateral view. 25. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 26. Aedeagus, ventral view. 27. Aedeagus, lateral view. 28. Female internal reproductive organs. Peralia hermanni. 29. Female internal reproductive organs. Scale = 0.1 mm. Abbreviation: LEP = lateral ejaculatory process, SpSd = spermathecal sac duct." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173538/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Fig. 
<number box="[942,973,850,876]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="20.0">20</number>
</figureCitation>
) quadrate, ending distal to posterolateral margin of epandrium; apicoventral area flat. Hypandrium reduced, heavily sclerotized, attached to anterior margin of gonocoxite. Gonocoxite ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[1225,1311,930,956]" captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 29" captionStartId="19.[264,382,1605,1629]" captionTargetBox="[296,1306,324,1572]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[249,1338,305,1582]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 29. Peralia vittata. 20. Tergite 8, epandrium, cerci, hypoproct, dorsal view. 21. Sternite 8, gonocoxite, ventral view. 22. Gonocoxite, dorsal view. 23. Gonocoxite, lateral view. 24. Gonostylus, lateral view. 25. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 26. Aedeagus, ventral view. 27. Aedeagus, lateral view. 28. Female internal reproductive organs. Peralia hermanni. 29. Female internal reproductive organs. Scale = 0.1 mm. Abbreviation: LEP = lateral ejaculatory process, SpSd = spermathecal sac duct." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173538/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Fig. 
<number box="[1281,1311,930,956]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="21.0">21</number>
</figureCitation>
) fused medially on posterior half, globular, sides rounded, posterolateral margin broadly rounded; dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[532,621,1010,1036]" captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 29" captionStartId="19.[264,382,1605,1629]" captionTargetBox="[296,1306,324,1572]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[249,1338,305,1582]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 29. Peralia vittata. 20. Tergite 8, epandrium, cerci, hypoproct, dorsal view. 21. Sternite 8, gonocoxite, ventral view. 22. Gonocoxite, dorsal view. 23. Gonocoxite, lateral view. 24. Gonostylus, lateral view. 25. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 26. Aedeagus, ventral view. 27. Aedeagus, lateral view. 28. Female internal reproductive organs. Peralia hermanni. 29. Female internal reproductive organs. Scale = 0.1 mm. Abbreviation: LEP = lateral ejaculatory process, SpSd = spermathecal sac duct." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173538/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Fig. 
<number box="[588,621,1010,1036]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="22.0">22</number>
</figureCitation>
), gonocoxal apodeme short, not extending beyond anterior margin, gonocoxal bridge narrow, attaching dorsal apodeme of aedeagus to medial margin of gonocoxite; lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[620,712,1090,1116]" captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 29" captionStartId="19.[264,382,1605,1629]" captionTargetBox="[296,1306,324,1572]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[249,1338,305,1582]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 29. Peralia vittata. 20. Tergite 8, epandrium, cerci, hypoproct, dorsal view. 21. Sternite 8, gonocoxite, ventral view. 22. Gonocoxite, dorsal view. 23. Gonocoxite, lateral view. 24. Gonostylus, lateral view. 25. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 26. Aedeagus, ventral view. 27. Aedeagus, lateral view. 28. Female internal reproductive organs. Peralia hermanni. 29. Female internal reproductive organs. Scale = 0.1 mm. Abbreviation: LEP = lateral ejaculatory process, SpSd = spermathecal sac duct." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173538/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Fig. 
<number box="[682,712,1090,1116]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="23.0">23</number>
</figureCitation>
) broad, globular; inner gonocoxal process (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 29" captionStartId="19.[264,382,1605,1629]" captionTargetBox="[296,1306,324,1572]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[249,1338,305,1582]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 29. Peralia vittata. 20. Tergite 8, epandrium, cerci, hypoproct, dorsal view. 21. Sternite 8, gonocoxite, ventral view. 22. Gonocoxite, dorsal view. 23. Gonocoxite, lateral view. 24. Gonostylus, lateral view. 25. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 26. Aedeagus, ventral view. 27. Aedeagus, lateral view. 28. Female internal reproductive organs. Peralia hermanni. 29. Female internal reproductive organs. Scale = 0.1 mm. Abbreviation: LEP = lateral ejaculatory process, SpSd = spermathecal sac duct." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173538/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Figs. 
<number box="[264,339,1130,1156]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="22.0" valueMax="23.0" valueMin="21.0">21–23</number>
</figureCitation>
) large, articulating with posterior margin of gonocoxite, broad, thick, tapering to posterior point, in lateral view clavate; ventral lobe (
<figureCitation box="[939,1031,1170,1196]" captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 29" captionStartId="19.[264,382,1605,1629]" captionTargetBox="[296,1306,324,1572]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[249,1338,305,1582]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 29. Peralia vittata. 20. Tergite 8, epandrium, cerci, hypoproct, dorsal view. 21. Sternite 8, gonocoxite, ventral view. 22. Gonocoxite, dorsal view. 23. Gonocoxite, lateral view. 24. Gonostylus, lateral view. 25. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 26. Aedeagus, ventral view. 27. Aedeagus, lateral view. 28. Female internal reproductive organs. Peralia hermanni. 29. Female internal reproductive organs. Scale = 0.1 mm. Abbreviation: LEP = lateral ejaculatory process, SpSd = spermathecal sac duct." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173538/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Fig. 
<number box="[1001,1031,1170,1196]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="21.0">21</number>
</figureCitation>
) short, fused medially. Gonostylus (
<figureCitation box="[415,503,1210,1236]" captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 29" captionStartId="19.[264,382,1605,1629]" captionTargetBox="[296,1306,324,1572]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[249,1338,305,1582]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 29. Peralia vittata. 20. Tergite 8, epandrium, cerci, hypoproct, dorsal view. 21. Sternite 8, gonocoxite, ventral view. 22. Gonocoxite, dorsal view. 23. Gonocoxite, lateral view. 24. Gonostylus, lateral view. 25. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 26. Aedeagus, ventral view. 27. Aedeagus, lateral view. 28. Female internal reproductive organs. Peralia hermanni. 29. Female internal reproductive organs. Scale = 0.1 mm. Abbreviation: LEP = lateral ejaculatory process, SpSd = spermathecal sac duct." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173538/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Fig. 
<number box="[472,503,1210,1236]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="24.0">24</number>
</figureCitation>
) broad, sinuate with apicomedial point; setae dark yellow. Aedeagus with dorsal apodeme (
<figureCitation box="[528,614,1250,1276]" captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 29" captionStartId="19.[264,382,1605,1629]" captionTargetBox="[296,1306,324,1572]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[249,1338,305,1582]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 29. Peralia vittata. 20. Tergite 8, epandrium, cerci, hypoproct, dorsal view. 21. Sternite 8, gonocoxite, ventral view. 22. Gonocoxite, dorsal view. 23. Gonocoxite, lateral view. 24. Gonostylus, lateral view. 25. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 26. Aedeagus, ventral view. 27. Aedeagus, lateral view. 28. Female internal reproductive organs. Peralia hermanni. 29. Female internal reproductive organs. Scale = 0.1 mm. Abbreviation: LEP = lateral ejaculatory process, SpSd = spermathecal sac duct." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173538/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Fig. 
<number box="[583,614,1250,1276]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="25.0">25</number>
</figureCitation>
) broad, anterior margin truncate; ventral apodeme (
<figureCitation box="[1228,1315,1250,1276]" captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 29" captionStartId="19.[264,382,1605,1629]" captionTargetBox="[296,1306,324,1572]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[249,1338,305,1582]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 29. Peralia vittata. 20. Tergite 8, epandrium, cerci, hypoproct, dorsal view. 21. Sternite 8, gonocoxite, ventral view. 22. Gonocoxite, dorsal view. 23. Gonocoxite, lateral view. 24. Gonostylus, lateral view. 25. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 26. Aedeagus, ventral view. 27. Aedeagus, lateral view. 28. Female internal reproductive organs. Peralia hermanni. 29. Female internal reproductive organs. Scale = 0.1 mm. Abbreviation: LEP = lateral ejaculatory process, SpSd = spermathecal sac duct." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173538/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Fig. 
<number box="[1284,1315,1250,1276]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="26.0">26</number>
</figureCitation>
) narrow, bifurcate anteriorly, reaching anterior margin of dorsal apodeme; distiphallus dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[420,507,1330,1356]" captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 29" captionStartId="19.[264,382,1605,1629]" captionTargetBox="[296,1306,324,1572]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[249,1338,305,1582]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 29. Peralia vittata. 20. Tergite 8, epandrium, cerci, hypoproct, dorsal view. 21. Sternite 8, gonocoxite, ventral view. 22. Gonocoxite, dorsal view. 23. Gonocoxite, lateral view. 24. Gonostylus, lateral view. 25. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 26. Aedeagus, ventral view. 27. Aedeagus, lateral view. 28. Female internal reproductive organs. Peralia hermanni. 29. Female internal reproductive organs. Scale = 0.1 mm. Abbreviation: LEP = lateral ejaculatory process, SpSd = spermathecal sac duct." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173538/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Fig. 
<number box="[477,507,1330,1356]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="25.0">25</number>
</figureCitation>
) broad basally, short, tapered posteriorly, apicolateral spines absent, lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[425,515,1370,1396]" captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 29" captionStartId="19.[264,382,1605,1629]" captionTargetBox="[296,1306,324,1572]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[249,1338,305,1582]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 29. Peralia vittata. 20. Tergite 8, epandrium, cerci, hypoproct, dorsal view. 21. Sternite 8, gonocoxite, ventral view. 22. Gonocoxite, dorsal view. 23. Gonocoxite, lateral view. 24. Gonostylus, lateral view. 25. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 26. Aedeagus, ventral view. 27. Aedeagus, lateral view. 28. Female internal reproductive organs. Peralia hermanni. 29. Female internal reproductive organs. Scale = 0.1 mm. Abbreviation: LEP = lateral ejaculatory process, SpSd = spermathecal sac duct." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173538/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Fig. 
<number box="[484,515,1370,1396]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="27.0">27</number>
</figureCitation>
) short, thick, sinuate; ejaculatory apodeme (
<figureCitation box="[1058,1149,1370,1396]" captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 29" captionStartId="19.[264,382,1605,1629]" captionTargetBox="[296,1306,324,1572]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[249,1338,305,1582]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 29. Peralia vittata. 20. Tergite 8, epandrium, cerci, hypoproct, dorsal view. 21. Sternite 8, gonocoxite, ventral view. 22. Gonocoxite, dorsal view. 23. Gonocoxite, lateral view. 24. Gonostylus, lateral view. 25. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 26. Aedeagus, ventral view. 27. Aedeagus, lateral view. 28. Female internal reproductive organs. Peralia hermanni. 29. Female internal reproductive organs. Scale = 0.1 mm. Abbreviation: LEP = lateral ejaculatory process, SpSd = spermathecal sac duct." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173538/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Fig. 
<number box="[1117,1149,1370,1396]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="25.0">25</number>
</figureCitation>
), anterior half narrow, extending well beyond anterior margin of dorsal apodeme, anterior margin rounded, in cross­section flattened dorsoventrally. Lateral ejaculatory processes (
<figureCitation box="[1220,1308,1450,1476]" captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 29" captionStartId="19.[264,382,1605,1629]" captionTargetBox="[296,1306,324,1572]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[249,1338,305,1582]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 29. Peralia vittata. 20. Tergite 8, epandrium, cerci, hypoproct, dorsal view. 21. Sternite 8, gonocoxite, ventral view. 22. Gonocoxite, dorsal view. 23. Gonocoxite, lateral view. 24. Gonostylus, lateral view. 25. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 26. Aedeagus, ventral view. 27. Aedeagus, lateral view. 28. Female internal reproductive organs. Peralia hermanni. 29. Female internal reproductive organs. Scale = 0.1 mm. Abbreviation: LEP = lateral ejaculatory process, SpSd = spermathecal sac duct." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173538/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Fig. 
<number box="[1276,1308,1450,1476]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="25.0">25</number>
</figureCitation>
), heavily sclerotized, curved dorsoventrally. 
<emphasis box="[772,990,1490,1515]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Female 
<taxonomicName box="[868,990,1490,1515]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Combretaceae" genus="Terminalia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="13" pageNumber="23" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">terminalia</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
. Anterior margin of sternite 
<number box="[264,278,1530,1556]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="8.0">8</number>
truncate; aedeagal guide present. Median lobe of tergite 
<number box="[978,992,1530,1556]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="9.0">9</number>
lacking setae. Furca (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 29" captionStartId="19.[264,382,1605,1629]" captionTargetBox="[296,1306,324,1572]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[249,1338,305,1582]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 29. Peralia vittata. 20. Tergite 8, epandrium, cerci, hypoproct, dorsal view. 21. Sternite 8, gonocoxite, ventral view. 22. Gonocoxite, dorsal view. 23. Gonocoxite, lateral view. 24. Gonostylus, lateral view. 25. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 26. Aedeagus, ventral view. 27. Aedeagus, lateral view. 28. Female internal reproductive organs. Peralia hermanni. 29. Female internal reproductive organs. Scale = 0.1 mm. Abbreviation: LEP = lateral ejaculatory process, SpSd = spermathecal sac duct." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173538/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Figs. 
<number box="[264,339,1570,1596]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="28.5" valueMax="29.0" valueMin="28.0">28–29</number>
</figureCitation>
) oval; common spermathecal duct shorter than furca; spermathecal duct narrow posteriorly becoming threadlike and convoluted before ending in large, oval spermatheca; spermathecal sac duct narrow, over five times length of furca before bifurcating to form two large spermathecal sacs; furcal projections absent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[264,1323,284,1756]" box="[312,658,1729,1756]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,527,1729,1755]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Immature stages.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
